The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                South Eastern Railway will run eight superfast special trains between Howrah and Puri from October 21 to 31. The Diwali special trains will stop at Kharagpur, Balasore, Bhadrak, Keonjhar, Cuttack, Bhubaneswar, Khurda Road and Sakshigopal. The trains will leave Howrah at 8.55pm.     Suranjan Das, the vice-chancellor of Calcutta University, and Amita Ray, a former professor of archaeology of the university, have been chosen as members of the Indian Council of Historical Research under the Union ministry of human resource development. The city-based historians will be part of an 18-member council, which was reconstituted on September 26.     Kashmira Khatun, 6, was run over by a truck on Friday on Baruipur-Kulpi Road while she was playing in front of the slum where she lived. The mishap occurred around 8.30pm. She was taken to a local health centre, where she was declared dead. The driver fled.    An unidentified 30-year-old man was found lying unconscious at Nimtala Ghat on Friday morning. Police took him to Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared dead.     Bhola Adhikari, 40, drowned in Matijhil pond in Entally around 12.45pm on Friday. Investigations revealed that the resident of Sil Lane had fallen into the pond in a drunken state. Adhikari was taken to NRS Hospital, where he was declared dead.    Officials of various universities in the state organised demonstrations on their respective campuses on Friday protesting the G.K. Chadha committees decision to exclude them from the purview of a committee set up to review the pay scales of university teachers and officials. The committee is unwilling to consider officials on a par with teachers.    Three persons were arrested in the Bowbazar area on Friday and a firearm and a dagger were seized from them. They were loitering around suspiciously, police said.                                                                                                                                                              
